China Children's Center will hold a series of activities to let children "high-tech" through "June 1" - Xinhua Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, May 20 (Huang Xiaoxi Zhou Shanshan) reporter learned from the China Children's Center on May 20, from May 28 to June 1, a series of activities to let children "high-tech" through "June 1" - Xinhua Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, May 20 (Huang Xiaoxi Zhou Shanshan). "Around June 1 Children's Day, the China Children's Center plans to hold a series of activities such as children's creative experience, children's visual arts festival, parent-child book carnival, so that children in the charm of cutting-edge technology to spend "June 1. It is understood that the activities held during this year's "June 1" Children's Day at the China Children's Center include the "Love Family Creative Cool" Children's Future Learning Carnival, the first Children's Visual Arts Festival, the "Book Carnival "The "Family Love Reading" picture book series, and other activities. Li Zhongming, deputy director of the China National Children's Center, said at a media briefing on June 1, 2016, that the "Love Family Creative" Children's Future Learning Carnival is the focus of this year's China National Children's Center's "June 1" celebration. "The event is focused on combining social innovation and family learning. The event focuses on the organic combination of social innovation and individual family creativity, through the participation of children and families to experience a variety of innovative educational activities, so that innovative practices become the cultural genes of the public family, so that "do-it-yourself" becomes a new way of learning and life for the majority of families. It is reported that the "Ai Jia Chuangku" children's future learning carnival includes "Dou Guo Chuangke" experience activities, the anniversary of the Old Cow Children's Exploration Museum and "explore the whole family love child Meng over June 1" activities, V R experience program for all, "creator tribe" interactive workshops and dozens of cutting-edge technology experience content.
